"v.消散，驱散 【英】 v. 消散,驱散(cause sb/sth to go in different directions) 【考】 disperse : reconvene / dismiss : reinstate(解散后重新召集/解 职后复职)反义词：focus(聚集) ; aggregate(聚集) 【例】 The crowd dispersed in all directions. v. (在不同方向上)消散; 使广大地散布或散发(如知识、粒子和光) 【记】dis向四面八方, sper分散, se: 散发 【类】disperse: reconvene = dismiss: reinstate 解散后重新召回 = 解职后复职 【反】focus(v 聚集); aggregate(v 聚集); channel(vt 引导) 【记】sperse 原指scatter，向四周洒；dis 向周围 + persons 人群 →将人群向四周驱散，使消失消散； 【相关】asperse 洒，诽谤(洒脏水)，洒圣水，disperse 分散，intersperse 散布, 点缀 disperse (v.)  late 14c., from Latin dispersus, past participle of dispergere ""to scatter,"" from dis- ""apart, in every direction"" (see dis-) + spargere ""to scatter"" (see sparse). The Latin word is glossed in Old English by tostregdan. Related: Dispersed; dispersing."
